s3 is storage account in the AWS where it acts as a pendrive and harddisk to our laptop

we can store any type in the s3 like pictures,videos,excel

Any file you store in s3 is called an object

and s3 provides 5 advantages Availability & Durability, Scalability, Security , Cost Effective , Performance 

Availabiliby - When you store one object in s3 aws by default that object is replicated in multiple places
So its 99.99999999999% Reliable 

Scalability - So you can store unlimited data in one bucket but each object should not be more than 5TB. 
But you can choose multipart upload to upload an object is size is more than 5 TB

Security - you can define your own policies of who can access the bucket

Cost Effective - Cost is very less

S3 is globally accessible we can do versioning of files and host the static websites.
